description:
Add comprehensive telemetry to Zephyr firmware for Renode testing.

## Files to modify:
- lichen/samples/lora_ping/src/main.c - test firmware
- lichen/samples/lora_ping/prj.conf - enable logging
- lichen/drivers/lora/lora_sx1262.c - if packet logging needed at driver level

## Requirements:

### 1. Enable logging in prj.conf
```conf
CONFIG_LOG=y
CONFIG_LOG_DEFAULT_LEVEL=3
CONFIG_LOG_BACKEND_UART=y
CONFIG_LOG_MODE_IMMEDIATE=y
# For hex dumps
CONFIG_LOG_BUFFER_SIZE=2048
```

### 2. Packet logging in lora_ping main.c
```c
#include <zephyr/sys/crc.h>

// Compute packet hash (CRC32 for simplicity, or use tinycrypt SHA256)
static uint32_t packet_hash(const uint8_t *data, size_t len) {
    return crc32_ieee(data, len);
}

// In TX path:
LOG_INF("[TX] len=%d hash=%08x", len, packet_hash(tx_buf, len));
LOG_HEXDUMP_DBG(tx_buf, len, "TX payload");

// In RX path:
LOG_INF("[RX] len=%d rssi=%d snr=%d hash=%08x", 
        ret, rssi, snr, packet_hash(rx_buf, ret));
LOG_HEXDUMP_DBG(rx_buf, ret, "RX payload");
```

### 3. Metrics tracking
Add static counters:
```c
static struct {
    uint32_t tx_count;
    uint32_t rx_count;
    uint32_t tx_bytes;
    uint32_t rx_bytes;
    uint32_t errors;
    uint32_t unique_hashes_seen;
    // Simple hash set (fixed size for embedded)
    uint32_t seen_hashes[64];
    uint8_t seen_hash_count;
} metrics;

// Track unique packets
static void track_hash(uint32_t hash) {
    for (int i = 0; i < metrics.seen_hash_count; i++) {
        if (metrics.seen_hashes[i] == hash) return;
    }
    if (metrics.seen_hash_count < 64) {
        metrics.seen_hashes[metrics.seen_hash_count++] = hash;
        metrics.unique_hashes_seen++;
    }
}
```

### 4. Periodic metrics dump
Every N seconds or at end:
```c
LOG_INF("METRICS: tx=%u rx=%u tx_bytes=%u rx_bytes=%u errors=%u unique=%u",
        metrics.tx_count, metrics.rx_count, 
        metrics.tx_bytes, metrics.rx_bytes,
        metrics.errors, metrics.unique_hashes_seen);
```

### 5. Parse announces to extract peer IID
```c
// If packet is announce (dispatch=0x15, type=0x01)
if (ret >= 13 && rx_buf[0] == 0x15 && rx_buf[1] == 0x01) {
    uint8_t *peer_iid = &rx_buf[5];
    LOG_INF("[RX] announce from %02x%02x%02x%02x%02x%02x%02x%02x",
            peer_iid[0], peer_iid[1], peer_iid[2], peer_iid[3],
            peer_iid[4], peer_iid[5], peer_iid[6], peer_iid[7]);
}
```

## Acceptance:
- west build succeeds with logging enabled
- Renode logs show [TX]/[RX] with hashes
- METRICS line parseable by fleet script
- Peer IIDs logged for announces
